  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.",
    "In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced onion, carrot, and celery and cook until the vegetables are tender.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional minute.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the cooked mirepoix mixture, chopped parsley, shredded gruyere cheese, heavy cream, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Mix well to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to an earthenware bowl.",
    "Bake the gratin in the preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the cheese is melted and bubbly."
